observations.recommendation:
Municipal Mayor issue a memorandum with appropriate timelines in requiring the Municipal Treasurer, in coordination with the Municipal Assessor, for the prompt updating of the RPTAR and preparation of the duly certified list of real property tax collectibles per taxpayer for submission to the Municipal Accountant so as resolve this recurring audit observation; 

Municipal Accountant to: 

Establish its accruals at the beginning of the year based on the certified list of collectibles on real property taxes as furnished by the Municipal Treasurer in compliance with Section 20 of the MNGAS for LGUs, IPSAS 1 and P.D No. 1445;

Investigate/trace the unreconciled differences, take appropriate actions by providing adjusting entries and monitor these accounts in order to prevent further discrepancies. A copy of the adjusting entries, if any, shall be furnished to the Audit Team, for evaluation; and

Maintain the subsidiary ledgers of SET and RPT Receivables accounts including its corresponding Deferred SET and RPT accounts.

We recommended and Management agreed that:
The Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Budget Officer provide explanation as to allowing these disbursements to be charged against the 30% QRF despite the absence of a Local Sanggunian Resolution and Declaration of State of Calamity and provide the lacking documentary requirements if necessary;
The LDRRM Officer ensure that Local Sanggunian Resolution and Declaration of State of Calamity shall be secured prior to utilization of the 30% QRF of the LDRRMF.

We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to issue a memorandum with appropriate timelines in requiring the Municipal Treasurer, in coordination with the Municipal Assessor, for the prompt updating of the RPTAR and preparation of the duly certified list of real property tax collectibles per taxpayer for submission to the Municipal Accountant so as to resolve this recurring audit observation;
We also recommended and the Municipal Accountant agreed to:
Establish its accruals at the beginning of the year based on the certified list of collectibles on real property taxes as furnished by the Municipal Treasurer in compliance with Section 20 of the MNGAS for LGUs, IPSAS 1 and P.D. No. 1445;
Investigate/trace the unreconciled differences, take appropriate actions by providing adjusting entries and monitor these accounts in order to prevent further discrepancies.  A copy of the adjusting entries, if any, shall be furnished to the Audit Team, for evaluation; and
Maintain the subsidiary ledgers of SET and RPT Receivables accounts including its corresponding Deferred SET and RPT accounts.

We recommended that the Management comply with the inventory accounting system/process including the use of prescribed forms of records and the reports in compliance with the Government Accounting Manual for LGUs and observe the following:

Perpetual Inventory System shall be used (Section 182 of the Manual);

The Accounting Unit and Supply Officer shall prepare and maintain the Supplies Ledger Card and Stock Cards, respectively. (Section 188 of GAM for LGUs, Volume I);

Inventory Custodian Slip (ICS) shall be issued for issuance of tangible items amounting to ₱15,000.00 and has a useful life of more than one year (Section 183 of GAM for LGUs, Volume I and Section 59 of GAM for LGUs, Volume II);

Requisition and Issue Slip (RIS) shall be prepared for every request of supplies and materials. Monthly RSMI shall be prepared and submitted to accounting unit for recording in the books; and

Inventories shall be recognized following the accounting entries prescribed under Section 192 of GAM for LGUs, Volume I.

We recommended that the Note 9-Financial Liabilities, disclosure in the Notes to Financial Statements be enhanced to include additional information on Loans Payable Account such as the following:

The name of lending institutions; 

Purpose of the loan;

The principal amounts;

Terms of the loan; and 

Loan status as of December 31, 2020.

