The Local Chief Executive cause the immediate liquidation of long outstanding cash advances of officers and employees pursuant to COA Circular No. 2012-004 dated November 28, 2012;
and
The Municipal Accountant obtain complete documentation of long outstanding cash advances to support the legal claim of the Municipality from the concerned officers and employees. When deemed necessary and on valid grounds, such as for deceased accountable officers, the Municipal Accountant request for write-off of unliquidated cash advances in accordance with the Revised Rules of Procedures of the Commission on Audit.

Provide funds for solid waste management’s operational activities on capacity building of households/residents, commercial, institutional and other establishments regarding proper solid wastes segregation, wastes collections and disposal of wastes in the temporary dumpsite or in the Final Disposal Area;
Disseminate information in every barangay regarding solid wastes segregation and disposal of wastes in the designated/temporary area to the Final Disposal Area by conducting seminars or other appropriate means that the management may determine; and
Assess the necessity of wastes collection in every barangay, provide schedules of regular collections, and undertake collection of wastes using the municipality’s equipment regularly.

Require all collecting officers to remit their collections regularly and intact to the Municipal Treasurer and observe the provisions in Section 69 of PD 1445 and Section 29 of NGAS Manual for LGUs, Volume I;
and
The Municipal Treasurer record and deposit her collections, and monitor the remittances made by every accountable officer in accordance with Section 69 of PD 1445 and Sec. 29, 30 & 31 of the NGAS Manual for Local Government Units, Volume I.

